<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1683,2037]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1792,1816]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after Edgar Alonso Chavarría Solano, the owner of the land where the species was taken, for all his help and kindness during our stay in 
<collectingCountry box="[678,804,1827,1851]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1683,2037]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,464,1863,1888]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The species groups with 
<taxonomicName box="[746,851,1864,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Litocladius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="floripa">
<emphasis box="[746,761,1865,1888]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[775,851,1864,1888]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">floripa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[905,1011,1865,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Litocladius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neusae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[905,1011,1865,1888]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">L. neusae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1018,1081,1864,1888]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1018,1081,1864,1888]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
based on the presence of spines on third palpomere; it can be separated from both by the presence of setae on M 
<number box="[1047,1054,1915,1929]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" value="3.0">3</number>
+ 
<number box="[1063,1071,1915,1929]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" value="4.0">4</number>
, Cu 
<number box="[1117,1125,1915,1929]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
and An, and by having 
<number pageId="7" pageNumber="46" value="110.0" valueMax="140.0" valueMin="80.0">80– 140</number>
setae in cell m 
<number box="[361,367,1953,1967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[376,385,1953,1967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" value="2.0">2</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
