</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,796]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[197,265,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Head.</emphasis>
AR 
<number box="[317,432,188,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="0.79" valueMax="0.85" valueMin="0.73">0.73–0.85</number>
. Ultimate flagellomere 
<number box="[696,794,188,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="322.0" valueMax="367.0" valueMin="277.0">277–367</number>
µm long. Temporal setae 
<number box="[1086,1100,188,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="9.0">9</number>
–12, 11 including 
<number box="[1302,1317,188,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="4.0">4</number>
–6, 5 inner verticals; 
<number box="[261,276,223,247]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
–3, 3 outer verticals; and 
<number box="[564,577,223,247]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
–5, 4 postorbitals. Clypeus with 
<number box="[945,958,223,247]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="5.0">5</number>
–7, 6 setae. Tentorium, stipes, and cibarial pump as in 
<figureCitation box="[285,397,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 17" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[241,1347,218,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 17. Litocladius chavarriai sp. n., male. 12 — tentorium, stipes and cibarial pump; 13 — third palpomere; 14 — thorax; 15 — wing; 16 — hypopygium, dorsal aspect; 17 — hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, dorsal aspect to the left and ventral aspect to the right." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200759/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Figure 
<number box="[366,397,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
. Tentorium 
<number box="[534,688,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="60111.5" valueMax="120116.0" valueMin="107.0">107–120, 116</number>
µm long; 
<number box="[809,836,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="18.0">18</number>
–23, 21 µm wide. Stipes 
<number box="[1122,1205,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="108.0" valueMax="118.0" valueMin="98.0">98–118</number>
µm long, 
<number box="[1325,1395,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="32.5" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="29.0">29–36</number>
(
<number box="[1412,1427,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
) µm wide. Palp segment lengths (in µm): 
<number box="[606,633,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="18.0">18</number>
–23, 21; 
<number box="[731,760,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="34.0">34</number>
–41, 38; 
<number box="[857,1013,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="60107.0" valueMax="120110.0" valueMin="104.0">104–120, 110</number>
; 
<number box="[1024,1122,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="113.5" valueMax="120.0" valueMin="107.0">107–120</number>
(
<number box="[1138,1154,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
); 
<number box="[1175,1271,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="127.0" valueMax="143.0" valueMin="111.0">111–143</number>
(
<number box="[1287,1304,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
). Third palpomere (
<figureCitation box="[252,334,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 17" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[241,1347,218,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 17. Litocladius chavarriai sp. n., male. 12 — tentorium, stipes and cibarial pump; 13 — third palpomere; 14 — thorax; 15 — wing; 16 — hypopygium, dorsal aspect; 17 — hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, dorsal aspect to the left and ventral aspect to the right." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200759/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[306,334,332,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number box="[411,424,332,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
–4, 4 sensilla clavata subapically, longest 
<number box="[903,917,332,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="9.0">9</number>
–14, 12 µm long; and with 
<number box="[1233,1274,332,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
apical spines, 
<number box="[151,179,367,391]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="25.0">25</number>
–36, 30 µm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,796]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[197,278,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[293,376,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 17" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[241,1347,218,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 17. Litocladius chavarriai sp. n., male. 12 — tentorium, stipes and cibarial pump; 13 — third palpomere; 14 — thorax; 15 — wing; 16 — hypopygium, dorsal aspect; 17 — hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, dorsal aspect to the left and ventral aspect to the right." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200759/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[345,376,404,428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antepronotum with 
<number box="[623,636,404,428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
–5, 4 setae. Dorsocentrals 
<number box="[931,959,404,428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="10.0">10</number>
–16, 12; acrostichals 
<number box="[1197,1224,404,428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="13.0">13</number>
–21, 16, composed of 
<number box="[185,198,439,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
–5, 4 anterior strong decumbent, 
<number box="[590,604,439,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
–4, 3 weak hair-like, and 
<number box="[908,922,439,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="7.0">7</number>
–14, 9 posterior scalpellate; prealars 
<number box="[1354,1369,439,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="4.0">4</number>
–6, 5; supraalar 
<number box="[261,276,476,500]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
. Scutellum with 
<number box="[466,480,476,500]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="7.0">7</number>
